<h1>Affiliate Disclosure</h1>

<p>
At everydaymoneylab, transparency is one of our core principles. This page explains how affiliate relationships may work on our website.
</p>

<h2>What Are Affiliate Links?</h2>

<p>
Some articles may contain affiliate links. This means that if you click on a link and make a purchase or sign up for a product or service, we may earn a commission at no additional cost to you.
</p>

<h2>Our Editorial Independence</h2>

<p>
Affiliate partnerships never determine what we write about or recommend. Our editorial decisions are made independently, and our goal is always to provide useful, accurate, and unbiased financial education.
</p>

<h2>Our Recommendation Policy</h2>

<p>
We only recommend products, services, or tools that we believe may provide value to our readers. However, every financial situation is different, and readers should always perform their own research before making financial decisions.
</p>

<h2>No Extra Cost to You</h2>

<p>
Using an affiliate link does not increase the price you pay. In many cases, it helps support everydaymoneylab while allowing us to continue producing free educational content.
</p>

<h2>Future Affiliate Partnerships</h2>

<p>
As everydaymoneylab grows, we may establish affiliate relationships with financial service providers, software companies, educational platforms, and other businesses whose products are relevant to our readers. Whenever affiliate links are used, appropriate disclosures will be included where required.
</p>

<h2>Questions?</h2>

<p>
If you have any questions regarding this Affiliate Disclosure, please visit our <a href="/contact/">Contact</a> page.
</p>

